<p>Dear readers of The Extra Mile - The Coronavirus has arrived in Illinois. Since Fridayâs blast on the Coronavirus, two new cases were discovered in Arlington Heights; and at least two school districts in Illinois have had to make the difficult decision to exclude both students and staff. Forty-eight schools in the state of Washington have been closed for cleaning. Illinois school districts must be prepared to make these decisions now. Chief among those decisions is under what circumstances schools should exclude students and staff. We do not recommend that schools solely rely on state and federal agencies in making this decision, as these agencies currently seem to be slow to react to local events. Rather, we recommend that each school district (or groups of districts) establish a task force to deal with when to exclude students and staff, as well as how to keep parents and the community informed and yet not cause a panic. This issue of The Extra Mile outlines issues schools need to consider and the steps schools need to take in dealing with the Coronavirus.</p>

